cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.MM

This paper discusses a technique for extracting content from web pages using the Document Object Model (DOM) tree. This technique is relevant to several areas of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), digital libraries (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on web content extraction, cs.IR is the most likely category, followed by cs.CL and cs.DL.
